The paper deals with resource allocation and optimization in a multi-tier network with different latency and reliability constraints for users. This falls under the domain of network optimization and communication systems, which are covered by cs.NI and cs.IT. The paper also proposes a learning-based heuristic method for solving the optimization problem, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of probabilistic guarantees for modeling user constraints and the consideration of multiple base stations for serving users suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of a support vector machine-based user association model suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
